    <td valign="top" class="AdminText"><a href="list_messages.asp?forumid=2&s_id=&m_id=&pagenum=2" target="main" class="AdminText" onMouseOver="MM_displayStatusMsg('Back to forum');return document.MM_returnValue" onMouseOut="MM_displayStatusMsg('Aegis Lux');return document.MM_returnValue"><img src="../Images/messageicon.gif" width="15" height="15" border=0></a>Posted 
      on: 30-03-2001 at 12:01:31 
      CET&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>
      <hr>
On march 29. Aegis sent a raiding party to the evil temple of Cazic-Thule. This was initiated by Archi, Robech and Arsante.<br><br>Now you highlevels think "What's special about THAT?"<br><br>Well, we're midlevel and we can't really raid Hate. All we CAN do is hate raids :) Because we read about all the good stuff you get there and we can't get our hands on it until level 47+.<br><br>What is important is to show that us mid-levels are able to plan a raid.<br><br>So what we did was arrange a mini-raid. Everything was planned. Time and place. Even arranged taxi pickups from various places in Norrath.<br><br>Everyone came.. except Toggun. He was lost in some timezone that's not on our converter, so Zeril joined instead.<br><br>The group was Kenween, Robech, Archi, Arsante, Zeril and Pepi. An all Danish wrecking crew :)<br><br>We entered Cazic-Thule and fought our way to the courtyard. We stood ground and realized that this was simply to easy. So we moved through the maze to the Archon Pyramid where we slaughtered ugly green lizards. We even had celebrity guests looking in. An Iksar monk (Sizzler) came and watched the show and started kicking those fleeing lizards. And with Robech, everybody was kung-fu fighting :)<br><br>Unfortunalty Kenween died (as he usually does when he's grouped with us small people) due to an invis that stopped working way to soon (sound familiar?). Luckily there was a level 56 cleric in the zone to give a 96% exp rez. The fighting went on and and exp came rushing in.<br><br>Then something odd happened. Not really sure what it was. But there were lizards everywhere. I think a beaten up lizard got help from his friends and brought 10 other lizards on top of us. Our fast thinking Wizmule immediatly hit the EVAC button and we gathered around him. Unfortunatly Archi and Kenween didn't make it to the dropship and was stranded.<br><br>Then came our celebrity guest number 2. Salorn, the mighty paladin came to save the day, but to late for Kenween who again was collected by the grim reaper. But again we was able to get a rez. After that he was collected by his wife. Bad things happen.. we continued for a while killing crocs.<br><br>What did we get from this raid then? Well, even though Kenween died twice, he still left with more exp than when he joined. We got two dings (Arsante and Pepi) and two steins for a mage focus quest I believe.<br><br>We had great fun, and everything worked as planned. Great teamwork. I even got a few good pictures. If you want me to, I can send them to Clarf for posting. <br><br>Happy hunting all.. Maybe next time we'll do Dalnir ;)<br><br><B>Pepi Lux</B><br><I>Cleric of light</I>
	<br>
